    <div class="story-card__description">
                        <a class="story-card__series" href="https://www.propublica.org/series/unplugged">Unplugged</a>
        
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/oil-orphan-wells-cleanup-playbook-siana-tom-ragsdale">
                                    The American Oil Industry’s Playbook, Illustrated: How Drillers Offload Costly Cleanup Onto the Public
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Oil executive Tom Ragsdale walked away from his old wells, making the pollution left behind the state of New Mexico’s problem. His tactics, however, are ubiquitous in the industry.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/mark-olalde">Mark Olalde</a>, illustrations by <span class="name">Peter Arkle</span>, special to <a href="https://www.propublica.org">ProPublica</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-12-30EST05:00">Dec. 30, 2024, 5 a.m. EST</time>
